# OS
.DS_Store

# Local-only macOS double-click launcher (regenerable; per-user convenience).
Launch CFD UI.command

# Quarantined report iterations (see reports/deep_acceptance/_archive_*/README.md).
# Keep these out of git history — regenerable, and the test-induced-pollution
# surface that produces them is tracked as a follow-up Codex-dispatch fix.
reports/deep_acceptance/_archive_*/

# Phase 5 audit-package builder staging dir (regenerable per build request).
ui/backend/.audit_package_staging/

# Phase 7a — Field post-processing capture (DEC-V61-031, 2026-04-21)
# Large VTK blobs from real OpenFOAM runs (typically 1-10 MB each).
# Keep the per-run manifest JSON so the backend route stays resolvable,
# but exclude the timestamped artifact tree under each case.
reports/phase5_fields/*/20*/

# Auto-regenerated dashboard snapshots — only canonical .html + manifest stay tracked.
# The deep_acceptance regen script writes a new timestamped snapshot every run;
# they accumulated to 170+ untracked files before being gitignored 2026-04-25.
reports/deep_acceptance/contract_status_dashboard_2*.html
reports/deep_acceptance/visual_acceptance_report_2*.html
reports/deep_acceptance/2*_visual_acceptance_package.md

# Raw solver audit run dumps (per-run, byte-different). DEC-referenced ones
# are explicitly force-added; everything else is regenerable from the solver.
reports/phase5_audit/2*_raw.json
reports/phase5_audit/live_*.log

# Phase 5 7c-service audit-report PDF output (regenerable; src/audit_package/manifest.py:342)
reports/phase5_reports/

# ADR-002 plane-guard runtime telemetry (per OPS-2026-04-25-001 §2 ownership;
# .jsonl files are per-process and should not pollute git).
# reports/plane_guard/ — runtime telemetry (.jsonl + .log) ignored;
# governance-class docs (baseline anchors, READMEs) tracked. Per-file
# pattern (rather than directory ignore + negation) because Git's
# negation rules cannot re-include files inside an excluded directory.
reports/plane_guard/*.jsonl
reports/plane_guard/*.log

# Codex raw execution logs — curated .md summaries are the tracked
# pattern under reports/codex_tool_reports/. Raw .log files are
# redundant; the verdicts are captured in the matching .md file
# and/or the relevant retrospective.
reports/codex_tool_reports/*.log

# Auto-corrections evidence trail — runtime emits a new YAML on every comparator
# deviation. They're a local audit aid; the DEC system tracks the canonical state.
# Force-add individual files if a specific deviation becomes audit-relevant.
knowledge/corrections/

# SOE / external proposal output artifacts — unrelated to harness core.
outputs/

# uv lockfile — project standard is .venv + pyproject.toml; uv.lock is local tooling.
uv.lock

# Codex-cadence override audit log — local-only (developer audit trail).
# Per-developer log; concurrent appends would conflict if tracked. The
# directory itself ships a tracked README explaining the contract.
.governance/codex_cadence_overrides.log
